  "prompt": "What's the best residential ISP in San Francisco?",
  "response": "The best residential ISP in San Francisco can vary depending on your specific needs, such as speed, reliability, customer service, and pricing. However, as of October 2023, here are some of the top contenders in the area:\n\n### **1. Sonic**\n- **Why it\u2019s great**: Sonic is a local ISP known for its commitment to privacy, excellent customer service, and fast fiber-optic internet. They offer gigabit speeds at competitive prices.\n- **Speed**: Up to 10 Gbps (in select areas).\n- **Pricing**: Transparent pricing with no hidden fees.\n\n### **2. AT&T Fiber**\n- **Why it\u2019s great**: AT&T Fiber offers high-speed internet with widespread availability in San Francisco. They provide reliable service and competitive pricing.\n- **Speed**: Up to 5 Gbps.\n- **Pricing**: Varies based on plan, often with promotional discounts.\n\n### **3. Xfinity (Comcast)**\n- **Why it\u2019s great**: Xfinity has extensive coverage in San Francisco and offers a variety of plans, including high-speed cable and fiber options. They also bundle TV and phone services.\n- **Speed**: Up to 1.2 Gbps.\n- **Pricing**: Affordable introductory rates, but prices increase after the promotion ends.\n\n### **4. Monkeybrains**\n- **Why it\u2019s great**: A local ISP offering affordable wireless internet with a focus on community and sustainability. They are a great option for those looking for an alternative to traditional ISPs.\n- **Speed**: Up to 1 Gbps.\n- **Pricing**: Competitive pricing with no long-term contracts.\n\n### **5. Google Fiber**\n- **Why it\u2019s great**: Google Fiber provides ultra-fast internet with simple, straightforward pricing. However, its availability in San Francisco is limited.\n- **Speed**: Up to 2 Gbps.\n- **Pricing**: Flat-rate pricing with no hidden fees.\n\n### **Factors to Consider When Choosing an ISP**:\n- **Coverage**: Check availability in your specific neighborhood.\n- **Speed**: Ensure the ISP offers the speeds you need for streaming, gaming, or working from home.\n- **Pricing**: Compare promotional rates and long-term costs.\n- **Customer Service**: Look for reviews on reliability and support.\n- **Privacy Policies**: Consider ISPs like Sonic that prioritize user privacy.\n\n### **Final Recommendation**:\n- **Best Overall**: **Sonic** for its fast speeds, transparency, and local focus.\n- **Budget-Friendly**: **Monkeybrains** for affordable and community-driven service.\n- **Wide Availability**: **Xfinity** or **AT&T Fiber** for reliable and widely accessible options.\n\nAlways check current reviews and availability in your specific area before making a decision!",
